{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783716644,"nonce":"zb9v9tp5FKV3bxyRKFhFlb+sG98=","message":"Update: the **churn half** is now resolved on all three backends by epic acb1c6d Phase 2's per-backend view-body introspection — PG (PR #96), MySQL (PR #97), and now **SQLite (PR #98, squash `4733f97`)**.\n\nSQLite view introspection (`introspect.rs::view()`) now reads the stored `CREATE VIEW` text from `sqlite_master.sql` and reconstructs the structural `ViewBody` via the reverse parser (`read_create_view`). With `canonical_view_body` reconciling the SQLite-specific divergences on both sides (schema-qualifier suppression → `SourceRef.schema = None`; the affinity result-pin fold; the `LIKE` case-sensitivity flag), the diff now reaches `desired_view == actual_view` for an unchanged view, so it emits **no** `CreateView` step — a view-carrying SQLite model re-plans to empty. The always-recreate `diff_views_global` branch only fires now for a body that genuinely cannot be reconstructed (graceful fallback).\n\nBecause a no-op publish no longer drops+recreates the view, it no longer wipes that view's `INSTEAD OF` triggers **on the no-op path**. (A real column-set/body change still drops+recreates, so the general trigger-wipe footgun for a *changed* view remains.)\n\nRemaining scope (still open, Phase 3): model triggers so a *changed* view's `INSTEAD OF` triggers are preserved/recreated across a genuine DropView+CreateView — the correct-layer fix PR #81 (closed band-aid) could not reason about without a trigger model. This bug stays open, subsumed by acb1c6d Phase 3.\n\nNote: PR #98 also fixed a rebuild-interaction 2.3 surfaced — an *unchanged* view over a table being rebuilt/renamed used to be pre-dropped only because body-unknown views were always re-created; the SQLite plan renderer now explicitly drops + recreates the transitive closure of such collateral views around a rebuild.","files":null}]}